### About me


I am second year PhD student at Arizona State University in the School of Criminology and Criminal Justice and a graduate research assistant in the Center for Violence Prevention and Community Safety. I earned my Bachelor of Arts degree from Bowling Green State University and my Master of Science degree from Arizona State University. My research interests include policing, program evaluation, and neighborhood ecology. My recent work has been published in the *American Journal of Public Health* and *Journal of Criminal Justice*. I am primarily working on the [Tempe First-Responder Opioid Recovery Project](https://www.publichealthpost.org/research/tempe-opioid-recovery/) which encompasses a collaborative response to the opioid crisis in Tempe, AZ.

